article.description: Jerri Taylor and Tudy Reed each scored 13 points to lead Xavier to a 68-55 win Saturday over Richmond.
article.headline: Xavier improves to 8-0 in Atlantic 10 with 11th straight win
article.linkText: Xavier tops Richmond for 11th straight victory
article.story:
RICHMOND, Va. -- Jerri Taylor and Tudy Reed each scored 13 points to lead Xavier (No. 21 ESPN/USA Today, No. 23 AP)
 to a 68-55 win Saturday over Richmond.

The Musketeers (20-4, 8-0 Atlantic 10) won their 11th straight game. Special Jennings added 11 points for Xavier.

Joanna McKnight scored 17 points in the second half to lead Richmond (17-7, 5-4). McKnight scored 14 points during a 22-10 spurt that pulled Richmond to 49-47 with 7:24 left. Three-pointers by Tyeasha Moss and Taylor combined with a layup by Jennings gave Xavier a 10-point lead with 4:56 remaining.

The Musketeers held Richmond to one field goal over a 7:23 period of the first half. Xavier led 28-19 at halftime.

The Spiders shot 38 percent from the floor against a top-ranked Xavier defense that is holding teams to 31.1 percent.
